1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:02,382
A production line stops.

2
00:00:02,382 --> 00:00:06,204
In seconds, a plan that looked perfect becomes impossible.

3
00:00:06,204 --> 00:00:09,368
CableTwin helps the manager see before deciding.

4
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:17,822
This is a fully synthetic Tunisian cable-factory scenario: three lines, ten orders, all planned on time.

5
00:00:17,822 --> 00:00:22,116
The prototype runs locally, offline, without a cloud service.

6
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:28,332
At 10:00, Line 2 stops for four hours.

7
00:00:28,332 --> 00:00:37,572
Without rescheduling, three orders are exposed, only seven stay on time, and projected cumulative delay reaches 620 minutes.

8
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,878
CableTwin does not hide one answer.

9
00:00:42,878 --> 00:00:48,787
Its symbolic, constraint-based planner builds three feasible routes from the same data.

10
00:00:48,787 --> 00:00:51,844
Service protects priority-weighted deadlines;

11
00:00:51,844 --> 00:00:55,105
Cost minimizes the illustrative comparison cost;

12
00:00:55,105 --> 00:00:57,550
Stability avoids line reassignments.

13
00:00:57,550 --> 00:01:03,732
Every route respects eligibility, duration, downtime, non-overlap and the planning horizon.

14
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:11,919
Before acting, the manager previews the revised Gantt and compares consequences.

15
00:01:11,919 --> 00:01:23,313
Service cuts projected delay from 620 to 140 minutes, reduces overtime from 180 to 30 minutes, and reaches 216 kilometres by 18:00 versus 188.

16
00:01:23,313 --> 00:01:29,572
Cost uses two line changes instead of three and has the lowest synthetic cost.

17
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:32,292
Nothing is sent to a machine.

18
00:01:32,292 --> 00:01:40,508
The production manager selects a route, approves it, and CableTwin records who decided, when, and which metrics supported the choice.

19
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:53,401
This working prototype is verified by nine tests and an independent exhaustive check of 17,856 candidate schedules.

20
00:01:53,401 --> 00:01:57,276
Next: a read-only shadow pilot on historical incidents.
